<br>
<!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.eqatlas.com/neriak.html">www.eqatlas.com/neriak.html</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--><br>
<br>
Setup is simple. Come in invisible, cross the bridge to just before the building indicated by 11. Wait until Lisvan X'Lottl comes out. He'll hang out for a minute, then head back in. Once he does, pop a pet(I preferred earth). Do not buff your pet in any way, or it will KS you, probably with some consistency. Again, wait til Lisvan comes along, then go to town on him. Take him out, then wait a minute or two and move into the cavern. There's a building inside with a portcullis. Evin X'Lottl spawns right behind the portcullis, and roams around the interior of that building. You may want to run in and fetch him if he's not there, so as to keep the respawn relatively even. Lisvan's spawn point is just before the bridge, outside the building. Once you've got it broken, park your pet on Lisvan's spawn point and gank em as they pop. <br>
<br>
As to actually killing them, you don't want your pet doing 50% damage, so you have to nuke a bit. Good news is that these guys only have about 1700 hit points. Basically, set your pet on them and nuke:<br>
<br>
Level 49-51: Use two Shock of Swords. Slow, but does the trick<br>
Level 52-53: Use two Chars. More damage and faster cast<br>
Level 54: Use either a Char and a Scars, or two Scars. Two Scars is trimming it a little close if there's a resist.<br>
<br>
They green out at 55.<br>
<br>
Earth pet generally has no trouble keeping them off of you. Some people favor air for stuns, since they're both wizards. Which reminds me, get your MR/FR/CR up as much as you can. They like to force shock, which interrupts casting, which equals xp lost to pet. They also cast some fire/ice based nukes which will hurt. A lot. Keep Phantom Armor and Elemental Armor up, and you should be ok in that respect.<br>
<br>
At higher levels (53-54 mostly) you can start working in the guard on the bridge and the necro (Something J'Narus, at 12 on map). The guard is a bitch though, very MR, sometimes he's an SK. Buff the hell out of your pet, don't nuke unless you can land a malosi. Chain pets if you need to, and let your pet have a share of xp. By 54, I could usually malosi him first or second try, and scars stuck pretty effectively. The J'Narus guy is a roaming necro, as long as you've got decent MR, he's as much of a pushover as the X'Lottl wizzies.<br>
<br>
Wow, this stretched out a little more than I expected. Oh well, have fun. It's great xp, but the loot is crap.<br>
